<![CDATA[
<p>Java FLAC Codec</p>
<p>jFLAC is a port of the Free Lossless Audio Codec (FLAC) library to Java. This library allows java developers to experiment and write programs that use the FLAC algorithms.</p>

<p>The <a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/jflac">jFLAC project</a> is hosted by <a href="http://sourceforge.net">SourceForge</a>.</p>

<p>You may want to explore the Java <a href="xref/index.html">source code</a>
and the <a href="apidocs/index.html">javadoc</a>.</p>

<p>The origional code for the Free Lossless Audio Codec (FLAC) can be found <a href="http://flac.sourceforge.net/">here</a>
on SourceForge</p>

<hr/>
